To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Pennsylvania Right-to-Know Law, 65 P.S. §§ 67.101 et seq., I hereby request the following records created or received between January 1st of 2024 and March 31st of 2026:

Permit Records: All internal and external communications, including but not limited to emails (and attachments), digital communications, electronic communications (e.g. Microsoft Teams chats, etc.), memos, and technical reviews, regarding the application, review, and issuance of Authorization ID numbers 1516120 and 1550971 and Permit numbers ESG295925002-00 and 117-22323; additionally include any communications as defined above mentioning the word Thornbottom;

Corporate Communications: All internal Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection and/or PADEP records referring to SENECA RESOURCES CO LLC or Seneca Resources Company, LLC or Seneca Resources or its parent corporation, National Fuel Gas Company, hereinafter collectively referred to as “Operator” regarding their fitness to hold permits, compliance history, or corporate integrity;

Statutory Compliance & Enforcement: All internal documentation, including inspection reports, internal legal reviews, and enforcement notes, discussing the Operator's compliance with, or potential violations of:
    1. 58 Pa. C.S. §§ 3211, 3218, or 3259;
    2. 18 Pa. C.S. §§ 901, 903, 3503, 3503(b), or 4904;
    3. Act of December 18, 2013, P.L. 1174, No. 166 - Surveyor's Right to Enter Act (2013);
    4. Act of June 2, 1937, P.L. 1189, No. 302 - Surveyors Entrance on Private Land (1937);

Inter-Agency/Local Communications: All communications between Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection and/or PADEP and officials or employees of Tioga County and/or COUNTY OF TIOGA and/or County of Tioga and/or TIOGA CNTY and Farmington Township and/or FARMINGTON (TOWNSHIP, TIOGA COUNTY) and/or FARMINGTON TWP TIOGA CNTY regarding the aforementioned permits or Operator;

Pending/Future Actions: All records regarding any currently pending, draft, or anticipated permit applications submitted by Operator in Farmington Township Tioga County and any that mention the word Thornbottom;

Financial & Benefit Records: All records identifying any gifts, donations, or "community benefit" payments provided by Operator to the agency or its officials, employees, agents or principals;

Response: If this request is denied in whole or in part, please provide a written response including the specific legal citation for the denial as required by Section 703 of the RTKL;

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes;

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request; I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not;

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter; I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

David Murray High

City of Evanston

